757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubrutas222.showPublicProfile?language=EN>brutas222</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/25/01 10:01:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Life after death?</span><hr size=1>    One of the more scary questions/thoughts.  I would like to hear how others think of life after death.  An eternity of adam and eve lifestyle?(no im not talking about the porn material)  Walking around picking vegies from the farm in the nude?  Psychotically waving our bodies around while praying to God for 23 of 24 hours in a day?  Pretending to be &quot;faithful&quot; to God so you are guarenteed life in &quot;heaven&quot;?  Feeling like you have no free-will cause God is micromanaging your life?  Scared life will be just plain-old boring?  Yep, I believe this is one of the major reasons why people don't feel good about a relationship with God.  Their insecurities about the &quot;unknown&quot;.  You know, that ignorance word.  We fear what we don't know.  So tell me what you imagine life after death to be like. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uogkrum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ogkrum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/26/01 2:27:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Life after death?</span><hr size=1>  I would like to think of Life after Death as a Dream Place,where past friends and family members that have passed on can be toghter,or maybe it takes you back to the 1 place in time that you loved .I love to think of the afterlife has a place that me and my grandmother would be toghter on some lake fishing like we used too..<br>
 <br>
 Only thing im afraid of is when i die,that i havent done all the things in life i could have done.I try to take risks and have fun and enjoy the time i have with my family and friends.I just dont understand the people that dont take any ricks.Who on there death bed is saying &quot;Im glad i didnt live my life like i had 1 day to live&quot;. <br>
 <br>
 I believe we should live everyday like there isnt a tomorrow.Maybe spend more time with family and friends telling them how much you love them.You never know when your life or theres will be cut short.<br>
<br>
 <br>
 /crys thinking about grandma<br>
   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulurikeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurikeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/26/01 8:59:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Life after death?</span><hr size=1> Life after death... why?<br>
