<br>
I have a feeling that the love and truth you have harnessed in life are what you will expect after death.  I believe life after death will have all of the fascinating obstacles and endevors of life as we know it.  Except that we won't be bound by our nature and twisted ideals of social acceptance.  I have known many people who have died (including family members) and would love to see them again.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufeathersilverthorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feather Silverthorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/26/01 11:19:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Life after death?</span><hr size=1> Life After death to me is simple.<br>
<br>
The impressions you leave. Friends, Loved ones, works both great and small, Writing, paintings, hand carved wood figurines, silly Everquest mythos and charecters. Ane most importantly Family.  If you have Children, love them, nurture them, read to them, watch movies with them, chase them around the yard yelling at the top of your lungs, make meories for them that are good and strong.<br>
