ill never encounter life after death.  Science in this case is limited.  Science is a system of logic which is based on sensual perception and thoughts.  It gives NO CREDABILITY to feelings.  Hence science is limited.   However truth combined with love(or thought combined with feeling) is NOT LIMITED.  Your passion is strong my friend.  Don't limit that passion and block it with thoughts of simple empirical data.  You are regarding feelings as inferior to thought by taking such an emperical stance(emperical, meaning scientific) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xamael>Xamael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/27/01 3:39:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Life after death</span><hr size=1> Dear all,<br>
